{{unreferenced|date=January 2013}}
'''Raï'n'B''' (written '''Raï&B''' and '''Raï/RnB''') is a musical genre that appeared in the 2000s in [[France]], with elements of both French contemporary [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] and [[Algeria]]n [[Raï]].

The DJ duo [[Kore & Scalp]] established the style and released the ground-breaking compilation album ''[[Raï'n'B (series)|Raï'n'B Fever]]'' in 2004 with the best examples of the genre that included [[Rap]], [[R&B]] and [[Raï]]. Many further albums were released in the series in 2006 and 2008 (produced by Kore & Bellek), 2009 special ''Même pas fatigué'' and Kore in 2011. Many of the tracks on the album ''Puissance Raï RnB 2012'' were produced by DJ Kim.



