{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}
'''Folk rhythm''' is a musical genre or style with roots in American [[folk music]] and [[rhythm and blues]].  It follows in the tradition of singer/songwriters like [[Townes Van Zandt]], [[Johnny Cash]] and [[Jack White (musician)|Jack White]] but sounds uniquely contemporary.  

Literally, the term '''folk rhythm''' refers to the genre's roots in [[American culture]] and the [[oral tradition]], (hence, folk) and the [[strum]] of guitar strings (rather than [[fingerpicking]]), as in [[rhythm guitar]].


