'''JUDUCA (Juegos Deportivos de Universidades Centro America)''' are a biennial multi-sport competition aimed at promoting sports in [[public university|public universities]] in [[Central America]]. The meet was first held in 2006 at the [[University of Costa Rica]]. Since then, JUDUCA has become an important sporting event among young Central American [[College athletics|college athletes]].

[[Student athlete|Student-athletes]] compete in 10 events: [[chess]], athletics, [[basketball]], [[soccer|football]], [[futsal]], [[volleyball]], [[karate]], [[tae kwon do]], [[judo]], and [[baseball]]. JUDUCA hosts 21 public universities from the 7 Central American countries. In 2016, JUDUCA will also invite some [[Caribbean]] nations.

JUDUCA 2016 will be in [[Honduras]].

